Package: aompls
Type: Package
Title: AOM-PLS Compact (PLS1) with Adaptive Operator Mixture and Optional Preprocessing
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("nirs4all contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                    email = "noreply@example.com"))
Description: Adaptive Operator Mixture Partial Least Squares regression
    (PLS1) with a compact 9-operator bank (Identity, Savitzky-Golay smoothing
    and derivatives, polynomial detrend, finite difference). Implements
    materialized SIMPLS with cross-validation-based operator and prefix
    selection. Supports optional Standard Normal Variate, Multiplicative
    Scatter Correction, Orthogonal Signal Correction, and Asymmetric Least
    Squares preprocessing. Performance-critical core is C++17 with vendored
    Eigen 3.4 (header-only, MPL2). Cross-validated against the Python
    reference implementation to machine precision.
License: CeCILL-2.1
URL: https://github.com/gbeurier/nirs4all
SystemRequirements: C++17
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.10), methods
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), jsonlite, knitr, rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 7.3.0
Config/testthat/edition: 3
NeedsCompilation: yes
